{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Ebunp9Fncewh5jQxhm15uf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me understand the migration scope. This is a **Quarkus** JSF+JPA address book app that needs to migrate to **Jakarta EE** (standalone, running on a Jakarta EE application server or embedded runtime). The key changes are:\n\n1. Replace Quarkus BOM/plugins with a standard Jakarta EE WAR deployment\n2. Change package names from `quarkus.tutorial` to `jakarta.tutorial`  \n3. Replace `application.properties` (Quarkus config) with `persistence.xml` (standard JPA)\n4. Move web resources from `META-INF/resources/` to `src/main/webapp/`\n5. Use an embedded server like WildFly/GlassFish in Docker or deploy as WAR\n\nLet me start implementing. I'll use an embedded approach with **WildFly** (most mature Jakarta EE implementation)."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":577,"cache_read_input_tokens":44132,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":577,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":712},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7644972d-de55-42ce-94f0-5092bba75a4d","uuid":"eec5ef26-c295-4ac7-ad95-139ce1c7799d"}
